   "body" : "Going further with ongoing wallet changes to rely on its own cached values instead of locking implicitly cs_main through Chain methods.\r\n\r\nThis PR introduce a behavior change, by setting new `m_is_ibd` value to false, wallet thinks being out of IBD until it proved wrong.  It let call `sethseed` while being disconnected, which may be blameworthty but as `createwallet` let you already generate a HD wallet without checking for IBD, we should go either way or the other, i.e can generate HD-seed without out-of-IBD or can't generate HD-seed without out-of-IBD. Thoughts ?",
